{"title_page": "Luynes, Bouches-du-Rh\u00f4ne", "text_new": "{{Other uses|Luynes (disambiguation)}}\n[[File:Eglise de Luynes by Malost.JPG|thumb|right|Church of Luynes]]\n'''Luynes''' is a [[village]] of the [[Bouches-du-Rh\u00f4ne]] ''[[d\u00e9partement in France|d\u00e9partement]]'' in southern [[France]]. It is located 4 [[km]] south of [[Aix-en-Provence]] at the intersection of the D7 and N8 roads. The village is perhaps best known for its prison and for its three international schools.  The ''N\u00e9cropole Nationale de Luynes'' is also located nearby.\n\nLuynes is bordered by the Massif du Montaiguet, which expands to Gardanne and Aix en Provence. It comprises chalky plateaux bordered by cliffs, forests of pines and oaks, and crops areas. In 1979 and 2005 the area was devastated by bush fires. Following these incidents, garrigue is now covering a wide area. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.myprovence.fr/en/travel-guide/entertainment/landscapes/aix-en-provence/54751-montaiguet-collines-de-gardanne|title=Mountains Montaiguet, Collines de Gardanne in Aix en Provence on My Provence|last=Tourisme|first=Provence|website=My Provence|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nThe private school Saint Fran\u00e7ois d\u2019assise is in Luynes.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20130206182952/http://www.aixenprovence.fr/Ecoles-privees \u00c9coles priv\u00e9es].\" Aix-en-Provence. February 6, 2013. Retrieved on September 4, 2016.</ref>\n\n{{Expand section|date=March 2016}}\n* [[International Bilingual School of Provence]]\n* [[Lyc\u00e9e International Georges Duby]]\n\n== Sport and Leisure ==\nIn June 2011 [[Zinedine Zidane|Zin\u00e9dine Zidane]] inaugurate his futsal sport complex: Z5. Z5 is also home to the gym Ar\u00e8ne Aix.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://z5sport.com/|title=Z5|last=Z5|website=Z5|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n== Prison ==\n[[Bernard Tapie]] was incarcerated in this prison for 165 days in 1997 following the VA-OM matter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lexpress.fr/informations/tapie-bernard-matricule-265449-g_626295.html|title=Tapie Bernard matricule 265449 G|date=1997-12-25|website=LExpress.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/*/http://www.aixenprovence.fr/Luynes Home page] {{in lang|fr}} (Archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121223131210/http://www.mairie-aixenprovence.fr/Luynes Commune of Luynes] {{in lang|fr}}\n{{coord|43|29|6|N|5|25|7|E|type:city_region:FR|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Luynes, Bouches-du-Rhone}}\n[[Category:Aix-en-Provence]]\n[[Category:Villages in Provence-Alpes-C\u00f4te d'Azur]]\n\n\n{{BouchesRh\u00f4ne-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Luynes (disambiguation)}}\n[[File:Eglise de Luynes by Malost.JPG|thumb|right|Church of Luynes]]\n'''Luynes''' is a [[village]] of the [[Bouches-du-Rh\u00f4ne]] ''[[d\u00e9partement in France|d\u00e9partement]]'' in southern [[France]]. It is located 4 [[km]] south of [[Aix-en-Provence]] at the intersection of the D7 and N8 roads. The village is perhaps best known for its prison and for its three international schools.  The ''N\u00e9cropole Nationale de Luynes'' is also located nearby.\n\nLuynes is bordered by the Massif du Montaiguet, which expands to Gardanne and Aix en Provence. It comprises chalky plateaux bordered by cliffs, forests of pines and oaks, and crops areas. In 1979 and 2005 the area was devastated by bush fires. Following these incidents, garrigue is now covering a wide area. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.myprovence.fr/en/travel-guide/entertainment/landscapes/aix-en-provence/54751-montaiguet-collines-de-gardanne|title=Mountains Montaiguet, Collines de Gardanne in Aix en Provence on My Provence|last=Tourisme|first=Provence|website=My Provence|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nThe private school Saint Fran\u00e7ois d\u2019assise is in Luynes.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20130206182952/http://www.aixenprovence.fr/Ecoles-privees \u00c9coles priv\u00e9es].\" Aix-en-Provence. February 6, 2013. Retrieved on September 4, 2016.</ref>\n\n{{Expand section|date=March 2016}}\n* [[International Bilingual School of Provence]]\n* [[Lyc\u00e9e International Georges Duby]]\n\n== Sport and Leisure ==\nIn June 2011 Zin\u00e9dine Zidane inaugurate his futsal sport complex: Z5. Z5 is also home to the gym Ar\u00e8ne Aix.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://z5sport.com/|title=Z5|last=Z5|website=Z5|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n== Prison ==\n[[Bernard Tapie]] was incarcerated in this prison for 165 days in 1997 following the VA-OM matter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lexpress.fr/informations/tapie-bernard-matricule-265449-g_626295.html|title=Tapie Bernard matricule 265449 G|date=1997-12-25|website=LExpress.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/*/http://www.aixenprovence.fr/Luynes Home page] {{in lang|fr}} (Archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121223131210/http://www.mairie-aixenprovence.fr/Luynes Commune of Luynes] {{in lang|fr}}\n{{coord|43|29|6|N|5|25|7|E|type:city_region:FR|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Luynes, Bouches-du-Rhone}}\n[[Category:Aix-en-Provence]]\n[[Category:Villages in Provence-Alpes-C\u00f4te d'Azur]]\n\n\n{{BouchesRh\u00f4ne-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ccthelion", "label": "safe", "comment": "sport and leisure", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luynes,_Bouches-du-Rh%C3%B4ne"}
{"title_page": "List of Parliamentary constituencies in Kent", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\nThe [[ceremonial county]] of [[Kent]], (which includes the [[unitary authority]] of [[Medway]]), is divided into 17 [[United Kingdom constituencies|Parliamentary constituencies]] - one [[borough constituency]] and 16 [[County constituency|county constituencies]].\n\n==Constituencies==\n\nThe results for the 2017 election were as follows:\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] \u2020|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] \u2021|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|[[Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color]]|[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] \u00a4|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n<!--All columns are for the 2019 election. See [[Parliamentary constituencies in Hertfordshire]] if you have trouble with the \"Member of Parliament\" and \"Nearest opposition\" columns.-->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=1|Constituency<ref group=nb>BC denotes borough constituency, CC denotes county constituency.</ref>\n!rowspan=1|Electorate\n!rowspan=1|Majority<ref group=nb>The majority is the number of votes the winning candidate receives more than their nearest rival.</ref>\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|[[Member of Parliament]]\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|Nearest opposition\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Map\n|-\n|[[Ashford (UK Parliament constituency)|Ashford CC]]\n|89,550\n|24,029\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Damian Green]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Dara Farrell \u2021\n|[[File:Ashford2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[Canterbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Canterbury CC]]\n|80,203\n|1,836\n|bgcolor={{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Rosie Duffield]] \u2021\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Anna Firth \u2020\n|[[File:Canterbury2007Consti