cies in Kent==\n===Used from 1983 to 1997===\n*[[Ashford (UK Parliament constituency)|Ashford]]\n*[[Canterbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Canterbury]]\n*[[Dartford (UK Parliament constituency)|Dartford]]\n*[[Dover (UK Parliament constituency)|Dover]]\n*[[Faversham (UK Parliament constituency)|Faversham]]\n*[[Folkestone and Hythe (UK Parliament constituency)|Folkestone and Hythe]]\n*[[Gillingham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gillingham]]\n*[[Gravesham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gravesham]]\n*[[Maidstone (UK Parliament constituency)|Maidstone]]\n*[[Medway (UK Parliament constituency)|Medway]]\n*[[Mid Kent (UK Parliament constituency)|Mid Kent]]\n*[[North Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|North Thanet]]\n*[[Sevenoaks (UK Parliament constituency)|Sevenoaks]]\n*[[South Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|South Thanet]]\n*[[Tonbridge and Malling (UK Parliament constituency)|Tonbridge and Malling]]\n*[[Tunbridge Wells (UK Parliament constituency)|Tunbridge Wells]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in the South East (region)]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{UK constituencies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Parliamentary Constituencies In Kent}}\n[[Category:Parliamentary constituencies in South East England| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of United Kingdom Parliamentary constituencies in England|Kent]]\n[[Category:Politics of Kent]]\n[[Category:Parliamentary constituencies in Kent| ]]\n[[Category:Kent-related lists|Parliamentary constituencies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\nThe [[ceremonial county]] of [[Kent]], (which includes the [[unitary authority]] of [[Medway]]), is divided into 17 [[United Kingdom constituencies|Parliamentary constituencies]] - one [[borough constituency]] and 16 [[County constituency|county constituencies]].\n\n==Constituencies==\n\nThe results for the 2017 election were as follows:\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]