nbridge Wells CC]]\n|74,816\n|14,645\n|bgcolor={{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Greg Clark]] \u2020\n|bgcolor={{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|&nbsp;\n|Ben Chapelard \u00a4\n|[[File:TunbridgeWells2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Boundary changes==\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Name!!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Boundaries prior to 2010\n|-\n|\n# [[Ashford (UK Parliament constituency)|Ashford CC]]\n# [[Canterbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Canterbury CC]]\n# [[Chatham and Aylesford (UK Parliament constituency)|Chatham and Aylesford CC]]\n# [[Dartford (UK Parliament constituency)|Dartford CC]]\n# [[Dover (UK Parliament constituency)|Dover CC]]\n# [[Faversham and Mid Kent (UK Parliament constituency)|Faversham and Mid Kent CC]]\n# [[Folkestone and Hythe (UK Parliament constituency)|Folkestone and Hythe CC]]\n# [[Gillingham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gillingham BC]]\n# [[Gravesham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gravesham CC]]\n# [[Maidstone and The Weald (UK Parliament constituency)|Maidstone and The Weald CC]]\n# [[Medway (UK Parliament constituency)|Medway CC]]\n# [[North Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|North Thanet CC]]\n# [[Sevenoaks (UK Parliament constituency)|Sevenoaks CC]]\n# [[Sittingbourne and Sheppey (UK Parliament constituency)|Sittingbourne and Sheppey CC]]\n# [[South Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|South Thanet CC]]\n# [[Tonbridge and Malling (UK Parliament constituency)|Tonbridge and Malling CC]]\n# [[Tunbridge Wells (UK Parliament constituency)|Tunbridge Wells CC]]\n|[[File:KentParliamentaryConstituenciesNumbered.svg|left|Parliamentary constituencies in Kent]]\n|-\n|}\n\nThe [[Boundary Commission for England]] retained these 17 constituencies{{when|date=May 2017}}, with changes to realign constituency boundaries with the boundaries of current local government wards, and to reduce the electoral disparity between constituencies.\n\nThey recommended two name changes: [[Gillingham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gillingham]] to\n[[Gillingham and Rainham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gillingham and Rainham]] to reflect the similar stature of the two towns, and [[Medway (UK Parliament constituency)|Medway]] to [[Rochester and Strood (UK Parliament constituency)|Rochester and Strood]] to avoid confusion with the larger Medway unitary authority. These changes were implemented at the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]].\n\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Proposed name!!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Current boundaries\n|-\n|\n# [[Ashford (UK Parliament constituency)|Ashford CC]]\n# [[Canterbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Canterbury CC]]\n# [[Chatham and Aylesford (UK Parliament constituency)|Chatham and Aylesford CC]]\n# [[Dartford (UK Parliament constituency)|Dartford CC]]\n# [[Dover (UK Parliament constituency)|Dover CC]]\n# [[Faversham and Mid Kent (UK Parliament constituency)|Faversham and Mid Kent CC]]\n# [[Folkestone and Hythe (UK Parliament constituency)|Folkestone and Hythe CC]]\n# [[Gillingham and Rainham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gillingham and Rainham BC]]\n# [[Gravesham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gravesham CC]]\n# [[Maidstone and The Weald (UK Parliament constituency)|Maidstone and The Weald CC]]\n# [[North Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|North Thanet CC]]\n# [[Rochester and Strood (UK Parliament constituency)|Rochester and Strood CC]]\n# [[Sevenoaks (UK Parliament constituency)|Sevenoaks CC]]\n# [[Sittingbourne and Sheppey (UK Parliament constituency)|Sittingbourne and Sheppey CC]]\n# [[South Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|South Thanet CC]]\n# [[Tonbridge and Malling (UK Parliament constituency)|Tonbridge and Malling CC]]\n# [[Tunbridge Wells (UK Parliament constituency)|Tunbridge Wells CC]]\n|[[File:KentParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|Proposed Revised constituencies in Kent]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Changes proposed for 2022==\nThe [[Boundary Commission for England]] proposed the following constituencies for the next United Kingdom general election (then assumed to be due in 2022) as part of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies]] in a combined region of Kent, Brighton and Hove, East Sussex and Medway.<ref>{{cite web |title=Final Recommendations - Volume 1 |url=https://boundarycommissionforengland.independent.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Final-recommendations-report.pdf |publisher=Boundary Commission for England |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n*[[Ashford (UK Parliament constituency)|Ashford]]\n*[[Bexhill and Battle (UK Parliament constituency)|Bexhill and Battle]]\n*[[Brighton Kemptown and Seahaven (UK Parliament constituency)|Brighton Kemptown and Seaheaven]]\n*[[Brighton Pavilion (UK Parliament constituency)|Brighton Pavilion]]\n*[[Canterbury and Faversham (UK Parliament constituency)|Canterbury and Faversham]]\n*[[Chatham and Malling (UK Parliament constituency)|Chatham and Malling]]\n*[[Dartford (UK Parliament constituency)|Dartford]]\n*[[Dover and Deal (UK Parliament constituency)|Dover and Deal]]\n*[[East Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)|East Thanet]]\n*[[Eastbourne (UK Parliament constituency)|Eastbourne]]\n*[[Folkestone and Hythe (UK Parliament constituency)|Folkestone and Hythe]]\n*[[Gillingham and Rainham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gillingham and Rainham]]\n*[[Gravesham (UK Parliament constituency)|Gravesham]]\n*[[Hastings and Rye (UK Parliament constituency)|Hastings and Rye]]\n*[[Hove and Regency (UK Parliament constituency)|Hove and Regency]]\n*[[Lewes and West Wealden (UK Parliament constituency)|Lewes and West Wealden]]\n*[[Maidstone (UK Parliament constituency)|Maidstone]]\n*[[North Kent Coastal (UK Parliament constituency)|North Kent Coastal]]\n*[[Rochester and Strood (UK Parliament constituency)|Rochester and Strood]]\n*[[Sevenoaks (UK Parliament constituency)|Sevenoaks]]\n*[[Sittingbourne and Sheppey (UK Parliament constituency)|Sittingbourne and Sheppey]]\n*[[Tonbridge (UK Parliament constituency)|Tonbridge]]\n*[[Tunbridge Wells and Crowborough (UK Parliament constituency)|Tunbridge Wells and Crowborough]]\n*[[Weald of Kent (UK Parliament constituency)|Weald of Kent]]\n\n==Historic representation by party==\nA cell marked \u2192 (with a different colour background to the preceding cell) indicates that the previous MP continued to sit under a new party name.\n\n===1885 to 1918===\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Independent Conservative/meta/color}}|[[Independent Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Independent Liberal/meta/color}}|[[Independent Liberal]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Unionist Party/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Unionist Party|Liberal Unionist]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{National Party (UK, 1917)/meta/color}}|[[National Party (UK, 1917)|National Party]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Constituency\n!1885\n!1886\n!''88''\n!''89''\n!1892\n!''93''\n!1895\n!''98''\n!''99''\n!1900\n!''01''\n!''03''\n!''04''\n!1906\n!Jan 1910\n!Dec 1910\n!''11''\n!''12''\n!''13''\n!''15''\n!''17''\n!''18''\n|-\n|[[Ashford (UK Parliament constituency)|Ashford]]\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[William Pomfret Pomfret|Pomfret]]\n| colspan=\"18\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Laurence Hardy|Hardy]]\n|-\n|[[Canterbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Canterbury]]\n| colspan=\"15\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[John Henniker Heaton|Heaton]]\n| colspan=\"6\" bgcolor=\"{{Independent Conservative/meta/color}}\" |[[Francis Bennett-Goldney|Bennett-Goldney]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Geor