reens]]\n|6,735\n|2.08\n| -\n|-\n|[[UK Independence Party|UKIP]]\n|2,629\n|0.81\n| -\n|-\n|[[Official Monster Raving Loony Party|Monster Raving Loony]]\n|667\n|0.21\n| -\n|-\n|[[Christian Peoples Alliance]]\n|301\n|0.09\n| -\n|-\n|[[Independent politician|Independents]]\n|160\n|0.05\n| -\n|-\n|'''Total'''\n|'''323,729'''\n|\n|'''6'''\n|}\n\n==Historical representation by party==\nA cell marked \u2192 (with a different colour background to the preceding cell) indicates that the previous MP continued to sit under a new party name.\n\n===1802 to 1837===\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"|[[Tories (British political party)|Tory]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"|[[Whigs (British political party)|Whig]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Constituency\n!1802\n!1806\n!1807\n!1812\n!''15''\n!1818\n!1820\n!1826\n!1830\n!1831\n!1832\n!''34''\n!1835\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Bedford (UK Parliament constituency)|Bedford]]\n|colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[William Lee Antonie|Antonie]]\n|colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Lord George Russell|G. Russell]]\n|colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Frederick Polhill|Polhill]]\n|colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Samuel Crawley|Crawley]]\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Samuel Whitbread (1764&ndash;1815)|S. Whitbread]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[William Waldegrave, 8th Earl Waldegrave|Waldegrave]]\n|colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[William Henry Whitbread|W. Whitbread]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"| [[Frederick Polhill|Polhill]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Bedfordshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Bedfordshire]]\n|colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Sir John Osborn, 5th Baronet|Osborn]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Richard FitzPatrick|FitzPatrick]]\n|colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Francis Russell, 7th Duke of Bedford|F. Russell]]\n|colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Lord Charles Russell|C. Russell]]\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[St Andrew St John, 14th Baron St John of Bletso|St John]]\n|colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Francis Pym (1756&ndash;1833)|Pym]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Sir John Osborn, 5th Baronet|Osborn]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Francis Pym (1756&ndash;1833)|Pym]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Thomas Potter Macqueen|Macqueen]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[William Stuart (1798&ndash;1874)|Stuart]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[Peter Payne (MP)|Payne]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Tories (British political party)/meta/color}}\"| [[William Stuart (1798&ndash;1874)|Stuart]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"| [[William Stuart (1798&ndash;1874)|\u2192]]\n|bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"| [[John Egerton, Viscount Alford|Egerton]]\n|}\n\n===1837 to 1885===\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Whigs (British political party)/meta/color}}\"|[[Whigs (British political party)|Whig]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n