mber of votes the winning candidate receives more than their nearest rival.</ref>\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|[[Member of Parliament]]\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|Nearest opposition\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Electoral wards<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2007/uksi_20071681_en_4|title=The Parliamentary Constituencies (England) Order 2007, page 4|publisher=Crown copyright|work=[[Office of Public Sector Information]]|accessdate=7 November 2009|date=13 June 2007}}</ref><ref>[[Boundary Commissions (United Kingdom)|Boundary Commission for England]] pp. 1004\u20131007</ref>\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Map\n|-\n|[[Bedford (UK Parliament constituency)|Bedford]] BC\n|71,579\n|145\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Mohammad Yasin (politician)|Mohammad Yasin]] \u2021\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Ryan Henson \u2020\n|[[Bedford Borough Council]]: Brickhill, Castle, Cauldwell, De Parys, Goldington, Harpur, Kempston East, Kempston North, Kempston South, Kingsbrook, Newnham, Putnoe, Queen's Park.\n|[[Image:Bedford2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=A small constituency, located north of the centre of the county.]]\n|-\n|[[Luton North (UK Parliament constituency)|Luton North]] BC\n|68,185\n|9,247\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Sarah Owen]] \u2021\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Jeet Bains \u2020\n|[[Luton Borough Council]]: Barnfield, Bramingham, Challney, Icknield, Leagrave, Lewsey, Limbury, Northwell, Saints, Sundon Park.\n|[[Image:LutonNorth2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=A small constituency south of the centre of the county.]]\n|-\n|[[Luton South (UK Parliament constituency)|Luton South]] BC\n|69,338\n|8,756\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Rachel Hopkins]] \u2021\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Parvez Akhtar \u2020\n|[[Luton Borough Council]]: Biscot, Crawley, Dallow, Farley,