d]]\n| colspan=\"6\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Adam Afriyie|Afriyie]]\n|-\n|[[Wokingham (UK Parliament constituency)|Wokingham]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[William van Straubenzee|van Straubenzee]]\n| colspan=\"11\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[John Redwood|Redwood]]\n|-\n|[[Slough (UK Parliament constituency)|Slough]]\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[John Arthur Watts|Watts]]\n| colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Fiona Mactaggart|Mactaggart]]\n| colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi|Dhesi]]\n|-\n|[[East Berkshire (UK Parliament constituency)|East Berkshire]] / [[Bracknell (UK Parliament constituency)|Bracknell]] (1997)\n| colspan=\"7\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Andrew James MacKay|A. MacKay]]\n| colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Phillip Lee (British politician)|Lee]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Phillip Lee (British politician)|\u2192]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|[[James Sunderland (politician)|Sunderland]]\n|-\n|[[Maidenhead (UK Parliament constituency)|Maidenhead]]\n| colspan=\"4\" |\n| colspan=\"8\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Theresa May|May]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Parliamentary constituencies in the South East (region)]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n;General\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.official-documents.gov.uk/document/cm70/7032/7032.pdf |title=Boundary Commission for England: Fifth Periodical Report |publisher=Crown Copyright |work=[[Boundary Commission for England]] |accessdate=6 November 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726095050/http://www.official-documents.gov.uk/document/cm70/7032/7032.pdf |archivedate=26 July 2011 }}\n*{{cite book|title=[[Boundaries of Parliamentary Constituencies 1885\u20131972]]|last=Craig|first=Frederick Walter Scott|authorlink=F. W. S. Craig|coauthors= |year=1972 |publisher=Political Reference Publications |location=[[Chichester]], Sussex |isbn=0-900178-13-2}}\n\n;Specific\n{{refend}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{UK constituencies}}\n{{Berkshire}}\n\n[[Category:Government and politics of Slough]]\n[[Category:Lists of United Kingdom Parliamentary constituencies in England|Berkshire]]\n[[Category:Politics of Berkshire]]\n[[Category:Parliamentary constituencies in Berkshire| ]]\n[[Category:Parliamentary constituencies in South East England| ]]\n[[Category:Berkshire-related lists|Parliamentary]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n[[File:EnglandBerkshire.png|thumb|200px|alt=A map of a country, divided into many smaller counties. One county, situated in a southern-central location, is highlighted in red|The county of [[Berkshire]] in relation to England.]]The [[ceremonial county]] of '''[[Berkshire]]''', (which is entirely made up of [[unitary authority|unitary authorities]] \u2013 [[Bracknell Forest]], [[Reading, Berkshire|Reading]], [[Slough]], [[West Berkshire]], [[Windsor and Maidenhead]] and [[Wokingham (district)|Wokingham]]) is divided into eight [[United Kingdom constituencies|Parliamentary constituencies]]: two [[Borough constituency|Borough constituencies]] and six [[County constituency|County constituencies]].\n\n==2019 constituencies==\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] \u2020|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] \u2021|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] \u00a4|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=1|Name<ref group=nb>BC denotes borough constituency, CC denotes county constituency.</ref>\n!